{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The future that we will create can be a future that we'll be proud of."},{"time":5000,"text":"I think about this every day; it's quite literally my job."},{"time":9000,"text":"I'm co-founder and senior columnist at Worldchanging.com."},{"time":15000,"text":"Alex Steffen and I founded Worldchanging in late 2003,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and since then we and our growing global team of contributors"},{"time":22000,"text":"have documented the ever-expanding variety of solutions"},{"time":26000,"text":"that are out there, right now and on the near horizon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"In a little over two years, we've written up about 4,000 items --"},{"time":36000,"text":"replicable models, technological tools, emerging ideas --"},{"time":41000,"text":"all providing a path to a future"},{"time":43000,"text":"that's more sustainable, more equitable and more desirable."},{"time":48000,"text":"Our emphasis on solutions is quite intentional. \n"},{"time":51000,"text":"There are tons of places to go, online and off,"},{"time":54000,"text":"if what you want to find is the latest bit of news"},{"time":56000,"text":"about just how quickly our hell-bound handbasket is moving."},{"time":61000,"text":"We want to offer people an idea of what they can do about it."},{"time":65000,"text":"We focus primarily on the planet's environment,"},{"time":69000,"text":"but we also address issues of global development,"},{"time":72000,"text":"international conflict, responsible use of emerging technologies,"},{"time":77000,"text":"even the rise of the so-called Second Superpower"},{"time":80000,"text":"and much, much more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"The scope of solutions that we discuss is actually pretty broad,"},{"time":85000,"text":"but that reflects both the range of challenges that need to be met"},{"time":89000,"text":"and the kinds of innovations that will allow us to do so."},{"time":93000,"text":"A quick sampling really can barely scratch the surface,"},{"time":96000,"text":"but to give you a sense of what we cover:"},{"time":98000,"text":"tools for rapid disaster relief,"},{"time":100000,"text":"such as this inflatable concrete shelter;"},{"time":102000,"text":"innovative uses of bioscience,"},{"time":104000,"text":"such as a flower that changes color in the presence of landmines;"},{"time":107000,"text":"ultra high-efficiency designs for homes and offices;"},{"time":110000,"text":"distributed power generation using solar power, wind power,"},{"time":114000,"text":"ocean power, other clean energy sources;"},{"time":116000,"text":"ultra, ultra high-efficiency vehicles of the future;"},{"time":119000,"text":"ultra high-efficiency vehicles you can get right now;"},{"time":121000,"text":"and better urban design, \n"},{"time":123000,"text":"so you don't need to drive as much in the first place; \n"},{"time":125000,"text":"bio-mimetic approaches to design that take advantage of"},{"time":128000,"text":"the efficiencies of natural models in both vehicles and buildings;"},{"time":132000,"text":"distributed computing projects"},{"time":134000,"text":"that will help us model the future of the climate."},{"time":136000,"text":"Also, a number of the topics that we've been talking about this week"},{"time":139000,"text":"at TED are things that we've addressed in the past on Worldchanging:"},{"time":143000,"text":"cradle-to-cradle design, MIT's Fab Labs,"},{"time":145000,"text":"the consequences of extreme longevity,"},{"time":149000,"text":"the One Laptop per Child project, even Gapminder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"As a born-in-the-mid-1960s Gen X-er,"},{"time":156000,"text":"hurtling all too quickly to my fortieth birthday,"},{"time":159000,"text":"I'm naturally inclined to pessimism. But working at Worldchanging"},{"time":164000,"text":"has convinced me, much to my own surprise,"},{"time":167000,"text":"that successful responses to the world's problems"},{"time":171000,"text":"are nonetheless possible."},{"time":173000,"text":"Moreover, I've come to realize that focusing only on negative outcomes"},{"time":178000,"text":"can really blind you to the very possibility of success."},{"time":182000,"text":"As Norwegian social scientist Evelin Lindner has observed,"},{"time":185000,"text":"\"Pessimism is a luxury of good times ..."},{"time":188000,"text":"In difficult times, pessimism is"},{"time":191000,"text":"a self-fulfilling, self-inflicted death sentence.\""},{"time":195000,"text":"The truth is, we can build a better world,"},{"time":198000,"text":"and we can do so right now."},{"time":200000,"text":"We have the tools: we saw a hint of that a moment ago,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and we're coming up with new ones all the time."},{"time":204000,"text":"We have the knowledge,"},{"time":206000,"text":"and our understanding of the planet improves every day."},{"time":209000,"text":"Most importantly, we have the motive:"},{"time":211000,"text":"we have a world that needs fixing, and nobody's going to do it for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"Many of the solutions that I and my colleagues seek out"},{"time":219000,"text":"and write up every day have some important aspects in common:"},{"time":224000,"text":"transparency, collaboration, a willingness to experiment,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and an appreciation of science -- or, more appropriately, science!"},{"time":232000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":233000,"text":"The majority of models, tools and ideas on Worldchanging"},{"time":237000,"text":"encompass combinations of these characteristics, so I want to give you"},{"time":240000,"text":"a few concrete examples of how these principles combine"},{"time":244000,"text":"in world-changing ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246000,"text":"We can see world-changing values in the emergence of tools"},{"time":250000,"text":"to make the invisible visible -- that is,"},{"time":253000,"text":"to make apparent the conditions of the world around us"},{"time":255000,"text":"that would otherwise be largely imperceptible."},{"time":259000,"text":"We know that people often change their behavior"},{"time":261000,"text":"when they can see and understand the impact of their actions."},{"time":264000,"text":"As a small example, many of us have experienced"},{"time":267000,"text":"the change in driving behavior that comes from having"},{"time":270000,"text":"a real time display of mileage showing precisely"},{"time":272000,"text":"how one's driving habits affect the vehicle's efficiency."},{"time":275000,"text":"The last few years have all seen the rise of innovations"},{"time":278000,"text":"in how we measure and display aspects of the world"},{"time":281000,"text":"that can be too big, or too intangible, or too slippery to grasp easily."},{"time":286000,"text":"Simple technologies, like wall-mounted devices"},{"time":290000,"text":"that display how much power your household is using,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and what kind of results you'll get if you turn off a few lights --"},{"time":295000,"text":"these can actually have a direct positive impact"},{"time":297000,"text":"on your energy footprint."},{"time":299000,"text":"Community tools, like text messaging, that can tell you"},{"time":302000,"text":"when pollen counts are up or smog levels are rising"},{"time":304000,"text":"or a natural disaster is unfolding,"},{"time":307000,"text":"can give you the information you need to act in a timely fashion."},{"time":312000,"text":"Data-rich displays like maps of campaign contributions,"},{"time":315000,"text":"or maps of the disappearing polar ice caps,"},{"time":318000,"text":"allow us to better understand the context and the flow"},{"time":322000,"text":"of processes that affect us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"We can see world-changing values in research projects"},{"time":328000,"text":"that seek to meet the world's medical needs"},{"time":330000,"text":"through open access to data and collaborative action."},{"time":333000,"text":"Now, some people emphasize the risks of knowledge-enabled dangers,"},{"time":338000,"text":"but I'm convinced that the benefits of knowledge-enabled solutions"},{"time":342000,"text":"are far more important."},{"time":344000,"text":"For example, open-access journals, like the Public Library of Science,"},{"time":349000,"text":"make cutting-edge scientific research free to all --"},{"time":352000,"text":"everyone in the world."},{"time":354000,"text":"And actually, a growing number of science publishers"},{"time":356000,"text":"are adopting this model."},{"time":358000,"text":"Last year, hundreds of volunteer biology and chemistry researchers"},{"time":362000,"text":"around the world worked together"},{"time":365000,"text":"to sequence the genome of the parasite responsible"},{"time":368000,"text":"for some of the developing world's worst diseases:"},{"time":370000,"text":"African sleeping sickness, leishmaniasis and Chagas disease."},{"time":374000,"text":"That genome data can now be found"},{"time":376000,"text":"on open-access genetic data banks around the world,"},{"time":378000,"text":"and it's an enormous boon to researchers"},{"time":380000,"text":"trying to come up with treatments."},{"time":382000,"text":"But my favorite example has to be the global response"},{"time":385000,"text":"to the SARS epidemic in 2003, 2004, which relied on"},{"time":389000,"text":"worldwide access to the full gene sequence of the SARS virus."},{"time":393000,"text":"The U.S. National Research Council"},{"time":395000,"text":"in its follow-up report on the outbreak specifically"},{"time":398000,"text":"cited this open availability of the sequence as a key reason"},{"time":402000,"text":"why the treatment for SARS could be developed so quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"And we can see world-changing values"},{"time":407000,"text":"in something as humble as a cell phone."},{"time":410000,"text":"I can probably count on my fingers the number of people in this room"},{"time":413000,"text":"who do not use a mobile phone --"},{"time":415000,"text":"and where is Aubrey, because I know he doesn't?"},{"time":417000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":419000,"text":"For many of us, cell phones have really become"},{"time":422000,"text":"almost an extension of ourselves,"},{"time":424000,"text":"and we're really now beginning to see the social changes"},{"time":426000,"text":"that mobile phones can bring about."},{"time":429000,"text":"You may already know some of the big-picture aspects:"},{"time":431000,"text":"globally, more camera phones were sold last year"},{"time":433000,"text":"than any other kind of camera,"},{"time":435000,"text":"and a growing number of people live lives mediated through the lens,"},{"time":438000,"text":"and over the network -- and sometimes enter history books."},{"time":442000,"text":"In the developing world, mobile phones have become economic drivers."},{"time":446000,"text":"A study last year showed a direct correlation"},{"time":449000,"text":"between the growth of mobile phone use"},{"time":451000,"text":"and subsequent GDP increases across Africa."},{"time":454000,"text":"In Kenya, mobile phone minutes"},{"time":456000,"text":"have actually become an alternative currency."},{"time":458000,"text":"The political aspects of mobile phones can't be ignored either,"},{"time":461000,"text":"from text message swarms in Korea helping to bring down a government,"},{"time":464000,"text":"to the Blairwatch Project in the UK,"},{"time":467000,"text":"keeping tabs on politicians who try to avoid the press."},{"time":469000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472000,"text":"And it's just going to get more wild."},{"time":474000,"text":"Pervasive, always-on networks, high quality sound and video,"},{"time":476000,"text":"even devices made to be worn instead of carried in the pocket,"},{"time":479000,"text":"will transform how we live on a scale that few really appreciate."},{"time":483000,"text":"It's no exaggeration to say that the mobile phone"},{"time":485000,"text":"may be among the world's most important technologies."},{"time":489000,"text":"And in this rapidly evolving context,"},{"time":491000,"text":"it's possible to imagine a world in which the mobile phone becomes"},{"time":494000,"text":"something far more than a medium for social interaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"I've long admired the Witness project,"},{"time":500000,"text":"and Peter Gabriel told us more details about it on Wednesday,"},{"time":504000,"text":"in his profoundly moving presentation."},{"time":507000,"text":"And I'm just incredibly happy to see the news"},{"time":510000,"text":"that Witness is going to be opening up a Web portal"},{"time":513000,"text":"to enable users of digital cameras and camera phones"},{"time":515000,"text":"to send in their recordings over the Internet,"},{"time":518000,"text":"rather than just hand-carrying the videotape."},{"time":520000,"text":"Not only does this add a new and potentially safer avenue"},{"time":524000,"text":"for documenting abuses,"},{"time":526000,"text":"it opens up the program to the growing global digital generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"Now, imagine a similar model for networking environmentalists."},{"time":535000,"text":"Imagine a Web portal collecting recordings and evidence"},{"time":538000,"text":"of what's happening to the planet:"},{"time":540000,"text":"putting news and data at the fingertips of people of all kinds,"},{"time":543000,"text":"from activists and researchers"},{"time":545000,"text":"to businesspeople and political figures."},{"time":547000,"text":"It would highlight the changes that are underway,"},{"time":549000,"text":"but would more importantly give voice"},{"time":551000,"text":"to the people who are willing to work"},{"time":553000,"text":"to see a new world, a better world, come about."},{"time":556000,"text":"It would give everyday citizens"},{"time":558000,"text":"a chance to play a role in the protection of the planet."},{"time":561000,"text":"It would be, in essence, an \"Earth Witness\" project."},{"time":565000,"text":"Now, just to be clear, in this talk I'm using the name \"Earth Witness\""},{"time":568000,"text":"as part of the scenario, simply as a shorthand,"},{"time":570000,"text":"for what this imaginary project could aspire to,"},{"time":573000,"text":"not to piggyback on the wonderful work of the Witness organization."},{"time":578000,"text":"It could just as easily be called, \"Environmental Transparency Project,\""},{"time":582000,"text":"\"Smart Mobs for Natural Security\" --"},{"time":586000,"text":"but Earth Witness is a lot easier to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"Now, many of the people who participate in Earth Witness"},{"time":591000,"text":"would focus on ecological problems, human-caused or otherwise,"},{"time":595000,"text":"especially environmental crimes"},{"time":597000,"text":"and significant sources of greenhouse gases and emissions."},{"time":601000,"text":"That's understandable and important."},{"time":603000,"text":"We need better documentation of what's happening to the planet"},{"time":605000,"text":"if we're ever going to have a chance of repairing the damage."},{"time":608000,"text":"But the Earth Witness project wouldn't need to be limited to problems.\n"},{"time":612000,"text":"In the best Worldchanging tradition,"},{"time":614000,"text":"it might also serve as a showcase for good ideas, successful projects"},{"time":619000,"text":"and efforts to make a difference that deserve much more visibility."},{"time":623000,"text":"Earth Witness would show us two worlds:"},{"time":625000,"text":"the world we're leaving behind,"},{"time":627000,"text":"and the world we're building for generations to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"And what makes this scenario particularly appealing to me is"},{"time":632000,"text":"we could do it today."},{"time":634000,"text":"The key components are already widely available."},{"time":636000,"text":"Camera phones, of course, would be fundamental to the project."},{"time":639000,"text":"And for a lot of us, they're as close as we have yet"},{"time":643000,"text":"to always-on, widely available information tools."},{"time":646000,"text":"We may not remember to bring our digital cameras with us"},{"time":648000,"text":"wherever we go, but very few of us forget our phones."},{"time":652000,"text":"You could even imagine a version of this scenario"},{"time":656000,"text":"in which people actually build their own phones."},{"time":658000,"text":"Over the course of last year, open-source hardware hackers"},{"time":661000,"text":"have come up with multiple models"},{"time":663000,"text":"for usable, Linux-based mobile phones,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and the Earth Phone could spin off from this kind of project."},{"time":670000,"text":"At the other end of the network, there'd be"},{"time":672000,"text":"a server for people to send photos and messages to,"},{"time":675000,"text":"accessible over the Web, combining a photo-sharing service,"},{"time":679000,"text":"social networking platforms and a collaborative filtering system."},{"time":684000,"text":"Now, you Web 2.0 folks in the audience know what I'm talking about,"},{"time":687000,"text":"but for those of you for whom that last sentence"},{"time":689000,"text":"was in a crazy moon language, I mean simply this:"},{"time":694000,"text":"the online part of the Earth Witness project"},{"time":697000,"text":"would be created by the users, working together and working openly."},{"time":702000,"text":"That's enough right there to start to build a compelling chronicle"},{"time":707000,"text":"of what's now happening to our planet, but we could do more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"An Earth Witness site could also serve as a collection spot"},{"time":714000,"text":"for all sorts of data about conditions around the planet"},{"time":717000,"text":"picked up by environmental sensors that attach to your cell phone."},{"time":720000,"text":"Now, you don't see these devices as add-ons for phones yet,"},{"time":723000,"text":"but students and engineers around the world"},{"time":725000,"text":"have attached atmospheric sensors to bicycles and handheld computers"},{"time":728000,"text":"and cheap robots and the backs of pigeons --"},{"time":732000,"text":"that being a project that's actually underway right now at U.C. Irvine,"},{"time":735000,"text":"using bird-mounted sensors"},{"time":737000,"text":"as a way of measuring smog-forming pollution."},{"time":740000,"text":"It's hardly a stretch to imagine putting the same thing"},{"time":742000,"text":"on a phone carried by a person."},{"time":745000,"text":"Now, the idea of connecting a sensor to your phone is not new:"},{"time":749000,"text":"phone-makers around the world offer phones that sniff for bad breath,"},{"time":752000,"text":"or tell you to worry about too much sun exposure."},{"time":755000,"text":"Swedish firm Uppsala Biomedical, more seriously, makes"},{"time":759000,"text":"a mobile phone add-on that can process blood tests in the field,"},{"time":763000,"text":"uploading the data, displaying the results."},{"time":765000,"text":"Even the Lawrence Livermore National Labs have gotten into the act,"},{"time":769000,"text":"designing a prototype phone"},{"time":771000,"text":"that has radiation sensors to find dirty bombs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"Now, there's an enormous variety of tiny, inexpensive sensors"},{"time":777000,"text":"on the market, and you can easily imagine someone putting together"},{"time":781000,"text":"a phone that could measure temperature, CO2 or methane levels,"},{"time":784000,"text":"the presence of some biotoxins --"},{"time":786000,"text":"potentially, in a few years, maybe even H5N1 avian flu virus."},{"time":792000,"text":"You could see that some kind of system like this"},{"time":794000,"text":"would actually be a really good fit"},{"time":796000,"text":"with Larry Brilliant's InSTEDD project."},{"time":799000,"text":"Now, all of this data could be tagged with geographic information"},{"time":802000,"text":"and mashed up with online maps for easy viewing and analysis."},{"time":806000,"text":"And that's worth noting in particular.\n"},{"time":808000,"text":"The impact of open-access online maps over the last year or two"},{"time":811000,"text":"has been simply phenomenal."},{"time":813000,"text":"Developers around the world have come up with"},{"time":815000,"text":"an amazing variety of ways to layer useful data on top of the maps,"},{"time":818000,"text":"from bus routes and crime statistics"},{"time":820000,"text":"to the global progress of avian flu."},{"time":823000,"text":"Earth Witness would take this further, linking what you see"},{"time":826000,"text":"with what thousands or millions of other people see around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"It's kind of exciting to think about what might be accomplished"},{"time":833000,"text":"if something like this ever existed."},{"time":836000,"text":"We'd have a far better -- far better knowledge"},{"time":838000,"text":"of what's happening on our planet environmentally"},{"time":840000,"text":"than could be gathered with satellites"},{"time":842000,"text":"and a handful of government sensor nets alone."},{"time":845000,"text":"It would be a collaborative, bottom-up approach"},{"time":847000,"text":"to environmental awareness and protection,"},{"time":850000,"text":"able to respond to emerging concerns in a smart mobs kind of way --"},{"time":853000,"text":"and if you need greater sensor density, just have more people show up."},{"time":856000,"text":"And most important,"},{"time":859000,"text":"you can't ignore how important mobile phones are to global youth."},{"time":863000,"text":"This is a system that could put the next generation"},{"time":866000,"text":"at the front lines of gathering environmental data."},{"time":869000,"text":"And as we work to figure out ways to mitigate"},{"time":872000,"text":"the worst effects of climate disruption,"},{"time":874000,"text":"every little bit of information matters."},{"time":877000,"text":"A system like Earth Witness would be a tool for all of us \n"},{"time":881000,"text":"to participate in the improvement of our knowledge and, ultimately,"},{"time":885000,"text":"the improvement of the planet itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"Now, as I suggested at the outset,"},{"time":889000,"text":"there are thousands upon thousands of good ideas out there,"},{"time":892000,"text":"so why have I spent the bulk of my time"},{"time":894000,"text":"telling you about something that doesn't exist?"},{"time":897000,"text":"Because this is what tomorrow could look like:"},{"time":900000,"text":"bottom-up, technology-enabled global collaboration"},{"time":905000,"text":"to handle the biggest crisis our civilization has ever faced."},{"time":909000,"text":"We can save the planet, but we can't do it alone -- we need each other."},{"time":913000,"text":"Nobody's going to fix the world for us, but working together,"},{"time":917000,"text":"making use of technological innovations and human communities alike,"},{"time":920000,"text":"we might just be able to fix it ourselves."},{"time":924000,"text":"We have at our fingertips a cornucopia of compelling models,"},{"time":927000,"text":"powerful tools, and innovative ideas"},{"time":930000,"text":"that can make a meaningful difference in our planet's future."},{"time":932000,"text":"We don't need to wait for a magic bullet to save us all;"},{"time":936000,"text":"we already have an arsenal of solutions just waiting to be used."},{"time":940000,"text":"There's a staggering array of wonders out there,"},{"time":942000,"text":"across diverse disciplines, all telling us the same thing:"},{"time":945000,"text":"success can be ours if we're willing to try."},{"time":948000,"text":"And as we say at Worldchanging,"},{"time":950000,"text":"another world isn't just possible; another world is here."},{"time":954000,"text":"We just need to open our eyes. Thank you very much."}]}]}